INSERT INTO `car_form_owners` VALUES (1,1,'Request to the Finance and Administration Department (FAD) a list of all necessary requirements and documents needed by existing sub-contractors','2023-09-15','None so far but this could pose a risk to the company, as the contractor may not be able to provide the required services in a compliant and/or reliable manners','N/A','2023-09-15','Conduct vendors accreditation for existing sub-contractors (MATEST & ALTEO) - August 23, 2023','2023-09-15','no','failure to conduct vendor accreditation for the hired contractor, which means that the contractor\'s qualifications and capabilities have not been verified.','2023-09-15','2023-07-17 16:00:00','2023-07-17 16:00:00'),(2,2,'To set a schedule for the conduct of refresher on the PTO Process which includes the following: introducing all IGRs and EGRs related to the process. How to fill up each document and what document will be used as reference.','2024-01-12','The timeline of the project was not followed and was adjusted. Staff’s workload overlapped.','Prioritize the revisions and review of the document to meet the allowed target timeline.','2024-01-12','Develop a detailed guide or checklist of important points for review.','2024-01-12','no','Errors usually occur in other projects and processes  including reports, certificates and other documents. It is recommended to use checklists and/or guides for self checking before internal review.','2024-01-12','2024-01-11 16:00:00','2024-01-11 16:00:00'),(3,3,'Verify all data entered into the KPI scorecard (2023) for the first-pass yield of plans/applications for any inaccuracies and revise appropriately','2024-02-29','Yes, it may misrepresent process performance and hinder the identification of areas for improvement.','verify all data entered in the scorecard and ensure the transparency and accuracy of data reported','2024-02-29','Establish guidelines for document quality checking - February 23, 2024 Establish monitoring of raw data to achieve more accurate KPI result - February 23, 2024 Cascade guidelines - February 29, 2024\"','2024-02-29','no','there might be some discrepancies in the reported process performance for others as well CA: verify all data entered and ensure the accuracy of data reported','2024-02-29','2024-02-05 16:00:00','2024-02-05 16:00:00'),(4,4,'Accomplished the review form to record the completion of the fourth round of quality checks of the documents.','2024-02-29','Yes, the absence of documentation can suggest that comments from the previous review may not be revised/corrected before client review, which could negatively impact the output and potentially lead to delays or rework.','ensure that all comments from previous reviews are corrected and documented','2024-02-29','Revise existing internal review form (FM No. 06-01-24) to not limit review rounds to third reviews - February 02, 2024 Establish guidelines for document quality checking - February 23, 2024 Cascade guidelines and revised form - February 29, 2024','2024-02-29','no','Documents that undergo multiple quality checks/reviews may not be properly documented and unintentionally neglected for other processes CA: Establish effective guidelines for quality checking of docs','2024-02-29','2024-01-22 16:00:00','2024-01-22 16:00:00'),(5,5,'Relocate obsolete forms to a separate folder, distinct from enrolled forms.','2024-02-29','Yes, using an obsolete form could lead to missing or incorrect information.','Restrict access to documents (forms, igrs, pm, etc.)','2024-02-29','Restrict enrolled forms folder on NAS to exclusive access by Department DC and Documentation Head. - February 9, 2024 Issue an internal memo regarding item 1 - February 16, 2024 DDC and DC Head will conduct a short refresher/orientation on department document control - February 29, 2024','2024-02-29','no','Inconsistencies in document control practices may exist for other processes beyond this one CA: regularly review process and update when appropriate','2024-02-29','2024-01-22 16:00:00','2024-01-22 16:00:00'),(6,6,'Revise IGR for tolerance for Metric Steel Tape under Metric Tape. Review Calibration Certificate of Equipment upon receipt and compare to the IGR for tolerance, mark it as “FIT FOR USE” if the tolerance is within range and make a recording in google sheet summary. For improvement, create a checklist for review before recording in the google sheet summary.','2024-03-25','There are other calibrated tools used for measurements in the 3rd to 4th quarter of 2023. This could have an impact on the accuracy of measurements as indicated on the Consulting outputs since there might be an inaccuracy of the results of measurement.','We use the equipment  from testing department which is externally calibrated.','2024-03-25','Correct the IGR by swapping the tolerances for Metric Steel Tape and Metric Tape in their respective sections. Consult an expert on this topic to review the reference properly. Provide training for relevant personnel on interpreting calibration tolerances and applying them to determine if equipment is fit to use. Create a checklist for review before recording in the google sheet summary Inform all relevant personnel about the correction made to the IGR (through email, department meeting, etc)','2024-03-25','no','If the above corrective action were not applied or implemented, there is a possibility of non-conformance to reoccur. See corrective action.','2024-03-25','2024-01-22 16:00:00','2024-01-22 16:00:00'),(7,7,'Segregate uncalibrated tools and label it “Calibration Expired Schedule External Calibration','2024-03-20','There are no immediate consequences associated with unused, expired calibrated equipment but it does not negate the potential for improvement.','Separating these items from the official pool and establishing dedicated storage would enhance clarity and mitigate future misuse.','2024-03-20','Designate a separate location and storage of pulled-out tools, label all equipment/tools as expired Use Logbook 4 (Logbook for Equipment In and Out & Other Docs) for the Pulled-out tools or equipment. Attached print-out copy of Calibration Plan to the Mechanical & Electrical Tools Cabinet, for easy distinction between - - - Expired tools and a valid one. Cascade this action to all consulting personnel.','2024-03-20','no','Apply corrective action to Electrical Tools.','2024-03-20','2024-03-10 16:00:00','2024-03-10 16:00:00'),(8,8,'Hold conduct of Internal Calibration Remove internally Calibrated Equipment from the official pool of Tools used in Consulting Services. Conduct thorough review on the WI.','2024-03-25','Yes, There are Internally calibrated tools used for measurements in 3rd to 4th quarter of 2023 by Technical Personnel. However, There is no Internally Calibrated Tools used for measurement on-site.','See correction.','2024-03-25','Temporary Corrective Action: Hold Internal Calibration. Apply External Calibration for the affected tools/equipment (Metric Steel Tape CMST8-01 & 02, Metric Tape CMT-01 & 02, and Laser Distance Meter CLD-01 & 02) Long term Corrective Action: Request for purchase or provision of Calibration table, Psychrometer and designated Calibration room (given they meet the requirements of NIST Handbook 44 - 2015 Linear Measure 5.52) Assign Personnel to the role of “Calibration Technician” and schedule a Training applicable on the Job description. Coordinate with the metrology team with regards to the overlapping.','2024-03-25','no','Similar issues with non-conformance may be encountered for other tools that undergo internal calibration, since as of now there is limited resources to perform calibration effectively. CA: See corrective action.','2024-03-25','2024-03-10 16:00:00','2024-03-10 16:00:00'),(9,9,'For the following: - Training hrs. per Envi & CCA Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Safety Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Security Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Health & Wellness Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Communications Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per BCP Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) to carry over trainings/awareness that was not implemented to 2023 work plan','2023-03-31','For the following: - Training hrs. per Envi & CCA Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Safety Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Security Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Health & Wellness Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Communications Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per BCP Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) no consequence yet aside from missed opportunities in competency building','N/A','2023-03-31','For the following: - Training hrs. per Envi & CCA Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Safety Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Security Subcommittee Member (Competency Building)- Training hrs. per Health & Wellness Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Communications Subcommittee Member (Competency Building)- Training hrs. per BCP Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) Implement a time management strategy to carry out proper training without conflicting with departmental commitments. Create effective methods and motivate members to make their own decisions by providing them with the resources and tools they need to excel. - March 31, 2023','2023-03-31','no','The same non conformity could potentially occur, until the corrective action above is implemented. Temporary action: During traction, announce in advance the upcoming training so the Managers and Subcommittee heads can collaborate with the schedules of the participant under each department.','2023-03-31','2023-03-30 16:00:00','2023-03-30 16:00:00'),(10,10,'Update Evidences of IGR No. 12-01-03 ESH Legal and Mandatory Requirements V 3.0 * 17 May 2022 for all classifications (OSH, Envi, COVID-19, etc.) of compliance obligations by February 10 2023','2023-03-28','Although evidences are not updated in time, monthly report of accomplishments has been done','Although evidences are not updated in time, monthly report of accomplishments has been done','2023-03-28','Update the PIC (Person-In-Charge) column of the IGR No. 12-01-03 ESH Legal and Mandatory Requirements V 3.0 * 17 May 2022 to specify the appropriate responsible department /subcomm /emergency response team (February 21, 2023) Recreate the Departmental list of ESH-related Compliances to merge them into a single Google Spreadsheet file separated into worksheets per department. ***with instructions*** (February 24, 2023) On top of the merged listings, the IMS officer is to implement a checklist method to track PIC completion of updating of evidence. This is using a Google Form containing the instructions to the process, link directing to the Departmental List, and checkboxes with questions confirming the completion of evidences. Set a cutoff date for the completion of evidence every 10th day of the month. Conduct a cascade meeting per department/group to formally assign to them the responsibility of updating their compliance evidence. (March 13-17, 2023) Follow up and ensure that the compliance evidences are updated for each sheet. (March 28, 2023)','2023-03-28','IA-062422-114','For compliances not in the ESH Legal but in the Monitoring of Legal and Mandatory Requirements. Corrective Actions: Ensure availability of evidence for the compliances in the Monitoring of Legal and Mandatory Requirements - Feb 17, 2023','2023-03-28','2023-03-27 16:00:00','2023-03-27 16:00:00'),(11,11,'a. For the succeeding ESH Facility Audit Report, all items required are already filled up in the May 2022 ESH Audit Report. b. All Sub-committee heads shall update their respective work plan on or before July 26, 2022 and to provide the necessary justification of the unmet deadline or to update the progress of plan.','2022-07-29','There are action plans that were not implemented e.g damaged ceiling at HR/Sales Office Deal: See correction item A Monitoring for the progress of the work plan is not being tracked. Deal: See correction item B.','a. For the succeeding ESH Facility Audit Report, all items required are already filled up in the May 2022 ESH Audit Report. b. All Sub-committee heads shall update their respective work plan on or before July 26, 2022 and to provide the necessary justification of the unmet deadline or to update the progress of plan.','2022-07-29','a.1 The Safety Officer of the Department should check the completeness of the ESH facility audit report including the ESH audit checklist signed by the Department Manager (July 15,2022) a.2 Revise ESH Audit Checklist to include Responsible Person and Timeline. Require the Department Safety Officers to fill the columns for the corrective actions, responsible person and completion date. (July 22, 2022) a.3 Discuss the action plans during ESH Monthly Meeting. (July 29,2022) b.1 Include ESH Work Plan update in the ESH Monthly Meeting agenda. (July 29,2022)','2022-07-29','no','no','2022-07-29','2022-07-28 16:00:00','2022-07-28 16:00:00'),(12,12,'Review existing risk assessment and EPR procedures and identify which potential emergencies is applicable in our operations onsite. (Sep. 15)','2023-10-13','so far, we haven’t met any concern yet relating to emergency scenarios / incidents. Usually, the client will assist our field personnel on the proper response following the client procedure and the field personnel will inform the head office.','N/A','2023-10-13','a. Research procedure on emergency management systems that include how to respond to client site-specific emergency scenarios (Sep. 22, 2023) b. Prepare a response procedure on the potential accidents, incidents and emergencies that may arise onsite. Include in the procedure the frequency of the review, including how often and when it should be reviewed (Oct. 13, 2023)','2023-10-13','no','as it may happen in any department that will have an activity onsite. (See corrective action above)','2023-10-13','2023-10-12 16:00:00','2023-10-12 16:00:00'),(13,13,'Review existing risk assessment and EPR procedures and identify which natural calamities may affect our operations. (Sep. 15)','2023-10-20','so far, we haven’t met any concern yet relating to emergency scenarios / incidents aside from earthquake where drills are conducted quarterly.','N/A','2023-10-20','a. Research procedure on emergency management system that include how to respond on emergency such as typhoon or flooding, earthquake and volcanic eruption, and other potential emergencies. (Sep. 22, 2023) b. Prepare procedure on proper response during different natural calamities. Include in the procedure the frequency of the review, including how often and when it should be reviewed (Oct. 20, 2023)','2023-10-20','no','as it may happen on any department that will go onsite. (See corrective action above)','2023-10-20','2023-10-19 16:00:00','2023-10-19 16:00:00'),(14,14,'Discussed the point for improvements/suggestions during the Management Review for ERT. Come up with action plans for the said improvements before the 3Q NSE Drill on September 7, 2023. (August 31, 2023)','2023-09-19','There were observed lapses in the preparedness of the organization when an earthquake occurred on June 15, 2023.','Since the earthquake incident has already happened and the response was found lacking, an incident report was created and deliberation of improvements were conducted. Additional action: see correction.','2023-09-19','a. Conduct a thorough risk assessment considering the process and timeline for the review of the incident and drill conducted. Include the discussion of  FM No. 12-02-10 - Earthquake Drill Plan for September 7,  (Sep. 5, 2023) b. Prepare or revise the procedure to reflect the changes. (Sep. 19, 2023)','2023-09-19','no','as it may happen on any drill to be conducted. (See corrective action above)','2023-09-19','2023-09-18 16:00:00','2023-09-18 16:00:00'),(15,15,'Set a meeting with the contractor to communicate the applicability of EPR (w/c emergencies) with them. (Sep. 19)','2023-11-10','So far, no significant emergency has happened yet that affects our contractors.','N/A','2023-11-10','a. Research procedure on emergency management systems on  how to manage and include contractors in our EPR (Sep. 22, 2023) . Prepare a procedure on how to manage and include contractors in our EPR. Include in the procedure the frequency of the review, including how often and when it should be reviewed (Oct. 20, 2023) . Revised the outsourcing and vendor accreditation process to include the EPR related requirements. (Nov. 10, 2023','2023-11-10','no','As we may not also consider other future contractors on our emergency response plan. (See corrective action above)','2023-11-10','2023-11-09 16:00:00','2023-11-09 16:00:00'),(16,16,'Conduct PM on EPR related equipment, and prepare PM report.','2023-10-30','Equipment (megaphone) was not functional at the time of emergency. (Earthquake incident)','ERT Head raises voice during the evacuation to be heard by all evacuees. Floor captains cascaded the message to their respective department and/or to ERT Heads (vise versa).','2023-10-30','a. Identify and formalize the responsible group  for the conduct of  preventive maintenance of EPR equipment. (Sep. 22, 2023) . Prepare PM checklist for the EPR equipment. (Oct. 13, 2023) c.Include in the ERT procedure the process of preventive maintenance, including on when to conduct the PM. (Oct. 30, 2023)','2023-10-30','no','no','2023-10-30','2023-10-29 16:00:00','2023-10-29 16:00:00'),(17,17,'A. Medical Emergency - Coordinate with the company physician for the data of disease transmission such as HIV before the review of risk registry and decide to change the risk rating in order to have an evidence. B. MNC - The risks from the actual emergency such as earthquake cannot be evaluated appropriately since these were not assessed – Consolidate all Earthquake-related risks in a single risk registry before 1Q2024 NSED C. Communication and Evacuation -  The risk registry for communication and evacuation has been updated, incorporating all possible evidence for the revisions. These revisions will then be cascaded to the communication and evacuation members. for C & D: Evacuation - Conduct thorough review of ERT Registry of Hazards and Aspects. Cascade Risk Registry to all the groups mentioned above and create minutes of meeting.','2024-04-30','No immediate consequence but new risks may be unmanaged due to lack of documented risk review','refer to item C&D on the correction','2024-04-30','A. Request for a learning session with Risk Management team and other ERT subgroup about Risk Registry on how to document evidences that supports the change in risk rating. (Communicate with other group and get a copy of data related to ERT-Medical before I decide to change the risk rating of the ERT-Medical risk registry.) B. The risks from the actual emergency such as earthquake cannot be evaluated appropriately since these were not assessed Create a specialized risk registry for earthquake scenarios. It should include all hazards related to preparation, response and recovery. The ERT MNC will be responsible in monitoring the actions contained in this registry Evaluation of the risk registry should follow the ESH Risk Management subcomm’s frequency of review. But, the ERT MNC shall initiate an evaluation of controls every after incidence of earthquake in the company. C. Communication/Evacuation The next review/changes of the Risk Registry for subcommittee will involve a regular meeting of the communication subcommittee, with all subcommittee members participating. Any changes made during this review must be properly documented, whether through minutes of meeting or other means of recording the changes. D: Evacuation Regularly review risk registry after every drill and actual emergencies Update Risk Registry if there are identified new risks or changes in rating based on the drill or actual emergencies Maintain records of risk review (M.O.M, Evaluation Sheet)','2024-04-30','no','A. Medical Emergency: No, as the team is already made aware that there should be a supporting evidences before adjusting the risk rating. B. Yes, Other Natural Hazards shall be included such as: Hydro-meteorological, Other Seismic Hazards, and  Volcanic. Create Separate registries for each in June 2024 C. Communication/Evacuation: No, the team is already made aware on the needed evidences. D: Yes, other teams may encounter the same issues in reviewing their respective registries.  refer to CA','2024-04-30','2024-04-29 16:00:00','2024-04-29 16:00:00'),(18,18,'A. Communication - a separate drill report will be created for the communication team\'s participation in the NSED drill on November 9, 2023.  B. Medical Emergency - create a separate report for the ERT Medical Emergency Group C. Fire Brigade Drill Report - documentation of the event was stored to google drive and the report to be created D. Logistics - create a report about the December 5 earthquake','2024-04-25','A. Communication & Medical Emergency - There are no immediate consequences, however, compliance will be required in future instances. Creating the drill report for the participated drill will resolve this. B. Fire Brigade - no immediate consequence. compliance concerns can potentially be raised due to lacking report. but can be mitigated by the evidences of the event C. Logistics - No immediate consequence but since there were no reports, no inputs were collected and analyzed from the earthquake incident. We’ll generate a report to include some data from the past incident and we’ll identify actions to improve our functions.','A. Communication & Medical Emergency - There are no immediate consequences, however, compliance will be required in future instances. Creating the drill report for the participated drill will resolve this. B. Fire Brigade - no immediate consequence. compliance concerns can potentially be raised due to lacking report. but can be mitigated by the evidences of the event C. Logistics - No immediate consequence but since there were no reports, no inputs were collected and analyzed from the earthquake incident. We’ll generate a report to include some data from the past incident and we’ll identify actions to improve our functions.','2024-04-25','A. Communication: To ensure that every time the ERT-Communication team participates in the drill will be documented, the team will create a form containing important details such as scenarios and areas for improvement. This will ensure proper documentation of the drill and prevent any oversight in reporting. B. Medical Emergency: Create a drill report form applicable for medical emergency group. C. Fire Brigade: A new secretary was assigned to the fire brigade committee Re-calibration of the functions of ERT and other ESH Committees - prioritization of activities C. Logistics: Identify objectives and improvement points of the ERT - Logistics and Facilities. This will be the basis for the creation of report template. Create work instructions for each function of the ERT - Logistics and Facilities group w/c also include the responsibilities.','2024-04-25','no','no','2024-04-25','2024-04-24 16:00:00','2024-04-24 16:00:00'),(19,19,'A. Security scheduled a Semi-annual drill regarding Bomb Threat in June 2024 and November 2024 B. Logistics: Schedule a drill with the next NSED schedule - March 25, 2024.','2024-05-31','A. No security related emergency was recently observed. Unpreparedness (lack of response plan testing of the team) have not yet resulted to aggravated risk. B. Logistics: Without the conduct of drills, the SOPs of the emergency team won’t be practiced and may reduce efficiency and effectivity. First, we must standardize the roles and actions of each function and each member. We then practice these and measure for effectivity.','A. No security related emergency was recently observed. Unpreparedness (lack of response plan testing of the team) have not yet resulted to aggravated risk. B. Logistics: Without the conduct of drills, the SOPs of the emergency team won’t be practiced and may reduce efficiency and effectivity. First, we must standardize the roles and actions of each function and each member. We then practice these and measure for effectivity.','2024-05-31','A. Security: The Incident Commander shall intervene with the team and organize their activities Clarify all uncertainties from members (which is which when it comes to function) Cascade plans for the year as listed in the ERT Workplan 2024  Obtain commitments from the members by having them sign a minutes detailing their responsibilities B. Logistics: Establish work instructions for the functions of ERT - Logistics & Facilities. Cascade the work instructions to each member. Join NSED drills to practice our team functions and check for effectiveness.','2024-05-31','no','A. Other functions of the team may suffer as well: Trainings, Preventive Maintenance. See corrective action to resolve. B. Logistics: When functions are not created, necessary activities may not be done. All activities done by the team must be documented and endorsed to every member of the team','2024-05-31','2024-05-30 16:00:00','2024-05-30 16:00:00'),(20,20,'Reintroduce the functions of the ERT - Logistics and Facilities to the members of the team, conduct a competency assessment  and create a training plan for 2024.','2024-04-20','No immediate consequence but a lack of training may impact the performance and effectivity of the ERT group in responding to emergencies.','To mitigate this, we first must set and standardize the function of the group, create a competency assessment  and create a training plan for 2024.','2024-04-20','Follow the correct process of identifying trainings needed for the team: - Conduct a competency assessment - Identify gaps and create a training plan. These plans will be reviewed for appropriateness and availability of provider.','2024-04-20','no','When training plans are not identified, there might be no trainings identified for the member or the trainings attended might not be effective for the needed competency. A proper assessment must be made first before identification','2024-04-20','2024-04-19 16:00:00','2024-04-19 16:00:00'),(21,21,'Met with the team members to relay their roles and functions in the team and clarified if they are indeed okay with being a member of the group.','2024-04-20','No direct consequence, but when a member is not aware of their functions, the function won’t be done during emergency.','N/A','2024-04-20','- Make sure to get the confirmation of each member on their membership to the ERT - Logistics and Facilities. -Since the functions of the committee involved functions of FAD as well, focus on getting members from FAD only but make sure to cascade the functions of the entire organization. -Setup the work instruction on each function, cascade to the team and practice the SOPs during NSED drills.','2024-04-20','no','When members are not aware of their functions, they won’t be able to perform well when needed as they are not guided by work instructions and have not practiced. To mitigate these, work instructions must be made for all functions and for emergency functions, these must be practiced.','2024-04-20','2024-04-19 16:00:00','2024-04-19 16:00:00'),(22,22,'- Since only Earthquakes are the only emergencies that recently occurred in our organization, consolidate all Earthquake-related risks in a single risk registry before 1Q2024 NSED. - Identify any lapses from our previous response in order to evaluate the respective risks associated with it.','2024-06-01','No significant injuries, damage during emergencies were recently observed. However, lack of review may result to aggravated risk and may cause worse impacts','See correction for dealing with the consequences','2024-06-01','- Draft a process wherein there is a frequent and formal review of the adequacy of the EPR. The process for Review of adequacy shall include the ff: - Adequacy of Resources including personnel, facilities, equipment, financial, communications - Information needs for all stakeholders - Responsibilities, roles, and chain of command across sectors - In the April 23, 2024 ESH/ERT meeting, the ERT MNC shall pitch the process to the team as headed by the Incident commander - Approval of the process','2024-06-01','IA-010924-142-ERT','no','2024-06-01','2024-05-31 16:00:00','2024-05-31 16:00:00'),(23,23,'Checked the status of the unclosed CARs and include these in the agenda on action plan follow-up meetings.','2023-05-30','With the delays in implementations issues that were previously experienced such as use of outdated forms, Delays in compliance, delays in utilities payments, delays in CAR closure, and low profitability were still experienced. There were improvements done (as specified in the previous CARs) to handle the unmet concerns but only partially done. Thus, some of the problems persisted.','N/A','2023-05-30','Create a reference per position on their: Responsibilities, Targets, Process flow, Controls, Frequency and schedule of actions / updating / reporting, Other responsibilities. Update these when new processes or responsibilities are added and delegate and cascade the actions to the process owners. These new processes must also have a schedule of review of implementation.','2023-05-30','no','New processes are not properly delegated to the process owners, there is a chance that the new process will not be implemented completely. To help address this, we could create a summary of responsibilities and schedule of activities which are easily accessible and viewable to them. Also, these processes must be monitored from them.','2023-05-30','2023-05-29 16:00:00','2023-05-29 16:00:00'),(24,24,'n/a','2023-06-28','No proper coordination','Who is the client? What is the concern? (case in point: Philippine Mining, CT Consigna Const.) - may mga client from Cebu na nasa list of AR, natatawagan kahit bayad na / natawagan ng FAD sa Manila pero hindi nasabihan si Cebu kaya natawagan ulit / PR# was changed to LZN, originally CEB When did the issue happen? February 2023 & April 2023 Where did the issue take place? (Write N/A if not applicable) Via phone call','2023-06-28','Day-1” calling should only include scripts for checking the correctness and accuracy of documents. Cascade this will all collection officers and branch admin officers so they know the risks Check for payment schedule may still be included in the script BUT the caller must always check from our systems if the client has not paid yet. Cascade to the team on how to check the payment status of clients; Event advanced payments. Ensure that the tagging of collection is timely to ensure correct status of ARs by changing the timing of recording from bulk update during fridays to live updating as collections are recorded. The FAD supervisor will also be the one to check the closing of ARs by the end of the day. Schedule regular process reviews on all processes of FAD. No need to add to KPI. Cascade the schedule to the whole team.','2023-06-28','no','When a step that is non-standard is done and the risks was not considered, similar situations where customer dissatisfaction may occur again. There are a lot of non-standard steps that may be made in our functions but one related to the situation is in the delivery of these invoices. Our delivery personnel might take initiative to ask our clients when they would pay the invoice they delivered. This may not present well to our clients especially when they’ve already paid the invoice. A regular process review must be done which also includes checking of risks vs practices done by the process owners.','2023-06-28','2023-06-27 16:00:00','2023-06-27 16:00:00'),(25,25,'Review the requirements submitted by the vendors including backup vendors which are critical to the operations such as WTL. Complete any missing requirements. Review & revise the guidelines on required documents.','2022-08-11','No consequence was experienced. But when necessary documents are not submitted, the qualifications of the vendors are not verified and may affect our operations negatively.','There are existing controls for quality but controls on ESH are insufficient and not implemented well yet. To manage these, we would need to review our ESH programs and how we’ll cascade them to the vendors and clearly define how we will implement the controls (if there are ESH programs that vendors don’t have, how can we help them?)','2022-08-11','Review the purchasing and accreditation procedures. Consult these processes with the IMS department. Clarify actions & escalations depending on submissions (including ESH requirements). Clearly classify vendors depending on their impact on the operations and set requirements based on impact.','2022-08-11','no','When the process is not clear and not reviewed under the requirements of the standard, required controls will not be implemented and quality and ESH performances of the vendors may not be at par with our quality and esh requirements. We need to clearly identify our requirements on our vendors and communicate these and how the impact our operations.','2022-08-11','2022-08-10 16:00:00','2022-08-10 16:00:00'),(26,26,'Get updates for all the existing and new findings of the preventive maintenance, make sure to encode them on the new report. Also, make sure that action plans are in the pipeline of the maintenance personnel.','2022-08-11','When facility improvements (and updates) are not recorded, there could be a mis-assignment of actions when the findings are found again. Also, without a monitoring of the actions plans to be done, the person incharge can’t be sure if the issues are being resolved or left out.','First, the facility audit report must be improved to reflect complete information about the findings. Secondly, the action plans of each findings must be listed and monitored frequently for progress.','2022-08-11','Improve the pm report to contain updates on the existing findings and to show due dates on when the actions can be done. (Not just until the next audit). Improve the monitoring system of the maintenance requests to completely show all requests and check the status of the requests – Not yet started, on-going, waiting for materials, on-hold, completed, and other statuses.','2022-08-11','no','other requests such as food requests don’t have clear instructions on how employees can proceed to request. These would be better managed when there are clear instructions and all requests can be monitored.','2022-08-11','2022-08-10 16:00:00','2022-08-10 16:00:00'),(27,27,'Jeffrey Camogao','2024-02-15','Late Arrival of Inspector','Na-late sa site last December 6, 2023 sa Maynilad dahil nasiraan ang originally issued na car. Naghintay muna ng kapalit before nakapag-deploy. Disappointed si client dahil expected matapos within the day ang inspection of 3 hoist.','2024-02-15','Client dissatisfaction, additional cost on our side or losses and delays in delivering the expected results of the client.','2024-02-15','no','Kapag hindi narereview agad ang mga equipment after use o pagkasaoli, hindi nakikita agad ang mga possible na naging defect sa mga gamit. Hindi na nagkakaroon ng enough time kung nakikita ang problem kapag kailangan nang gamitin ang equipment. Kailangan makapagsetup ng checking sa lahat ng equipment tuwing sinasauli para maayos agad ang mga posibleng problema.','2024-02-15','2024-02-14 16:00:00','2024-02-14 16:00:00'),(28,28,'No correction. Arrived on site as soon as possible and when the client requested for an overtime to finish the inspection, the team allowed it.','2024-07-25','Client will remember that we are late and might prove to be a decision point in the future.','Request a visit with client to refresh this experience with a better one.','2024-07-25','Advise the drivers on this risk, that they may consider that their phones may be played on by their children and their alarms be shutoff. Assign the guards to call the drivers when they are still not in the area on their call time (30 mins before departure). Since drivers may not be able to answer these calls when already driving towards the office, it is encouraged that they advise the team or the guards that they’ll be late. Advise the operations teams and deployment personnel to call the drivers and/or the dispatch officer of FAD when drivers are not yet in the office.','2024-07-25','no','When the operations team would be late, the drivers w/ the help of the guards must call the team or the deployment personnel of the operations dept.','2024-07-25','2024-07-24 16:00:00','2024-07-24 16:00:00'),(29,29,'- Continuously following up with the person in charge of training and the department head about the progress of employee training (Training Plan 2022) that happened on December 2, 2022. - Send the old Training Plan from 2022 to the department head to use as a guide and add it to the Training Plan for 2023. (January 7, 2023)','2023-02-06','There is no improvement in the competency of employees, which can lead to inefficiency in the performance of their roles.','Alternative conduct of Internal Trainings / Learning Session.','2023-02-06','1. Revise Procedure Manual on “Manage Training System” and includes; (February 3, 2023) Discuss Competency Assessment with HR Manager / Supervisor including the employee. Evaluate Training Plan with HR Manager / Supervisor. Discuss Training Plan with HR Manager / Supervisor including the employee. 2. Conduct Monthly Meeting with Training Point Person per Department. (February 27, 2023)','2023-02-06','IA-062921-59-HR','It can lead to lack of continuous improvement. Regularly review and check training program/plan based on competency assessment result.','2023-02-06','2023-02-05 16:00:00','2023-02-05 16:00:00'),(30,30,'Immediately request the inadequate amount to FAD (for the completion of salary)  and give it to the concerned personnel.','2024-01-31','The concerned employee might have financial stress due to inadequate salary. Negative feeling of concerned employees towards the company. Employees may become disengaged and lead to internal conflicts.','From the moment HR became aware of the concern, the HR immediately addressed the concern by reviewing the computation and requested money from FAD, HR also apologized to the employee and explained the incident.','2024-01-31','Establish and implement Payroll automation to lessen the Manual labor on computation and encoding of details (employee’s salary). Automatic computation of working days, Overtime, Night diff. and etc. Generated details from DTR will automatically reflect to the Payroll Template. To allow time for sufficient double checking of Payroll entry, push department heads to submit at the given deadline (1 to 1 and half days) after every cut-off.','2024-01-31','NA-100422-332-HR','no','2024-01-31','2024-01-30 16:00:00','2024-01-30 16:00:00'),(31,31,'Review and inclusion of action plans in the strat plan adjustment of schedule “WEM Training” Capability WEM Equipment Rental Services','2022-02-15','for both 1 and 2. the effect is that the final goal of strategic growth and to  expand the revenue is affected. WEM Training will allow for us to lessen our reliance on the trainings conducted by OSHC - ECD. WEM Rental will offer another avenue for us to cater to clients','N/A','2022-02-15','WEM Training. The project implementation will be guided by experts on the matter. Ma’am Anna Tubelonia on the development of the training module. Guided by IMS and consultant on monitoring the implementation. WEM Equipment Rental. Assessment of Capabilities and stricter monitoring of progress. documentation of assessment - deliberate: capabilities needed while there is no assigned personnel, Manager take charge of the development','2022-02-15','no','Skills of manager in project management to be refined. attend udemy learning program on project management','2022-02-15','2022-02-14 16:00:00','2022-02-14 16:00:00'),(32,32,'None','2024-04-30','Affected sample RD-IBGC-11 initially encoded as D-3973 (from COC), but encoded during sample login adjustment as D-3573 for preweights fetching returned 0.100 mg result instead of 0.01 mg. The error occurred in both the analysis worksheet (sample analyzed on Nov 14, 2023) and final report (released and endorsed on Nov 20, 2023). With the inherent validations and process checks failing, the error was only detected and raised on Dec 05, 2023 during regular data cleaning of D - Dust Pre-weights Masterlist.','The discovered error was reported in the subsequent traction meeting (Dec 11, 2023) and with further discussions, reported to IMS and issued a corrective action request on the dates specified above (Dec 18, 2023 and Jan 12, 2024, respectively). The reported value may reflect tenfold increase, but relatively still presents a dust reading below action level (0.5 TLV), especially compared to the 5 mg/m3 TLV equivalent of 0.375 mg from a 30-min. aluminum cyclone sampling.','2024-04-30','Correction of validation logic to join Batch No. validation with Lab Code validation instead of separate row-wise checking - 02/23/2024. Designated laboratory assistant for sample login - 03/22/2024. More comprehensive quality checking of worksheets, reports, masterlists from raw data (COC, SMF, email requests) - 02/29/2024. Strategies to boost laboratory profitability (more regular and relational client engagement from Sales & Marketing, analysis costing updated with general & administrative expenses, sourcing alternative suppliers, additional income streams through accreditations) - 07/29/2024. Increased capacity building to enable dedicated