uired. The Sr. IMS officer shall document the comparison. Update ESH Legal and Mandatory Requirements as appropriate','2024-04-30','no','The potential nonconformity is in other Reportorials sent monthly or quarterly. Include these reportorials in the review to be conducted as described in the CA','2024-04-30','2024-04-29 16:00:00','2024-04-29 16:00:00'),(43,43,'A. Unmet Targets 2023 for On-time Verification of CARs at 51% against 100%. - Ensure that all open CARs are verified as of May 31, 2024. B. Late Issuance of CARs for Unmet Targets 2023. - Ensure that all issued CARs are submitted by May 6, 2024','2024-07-19','A. Actions from open CARs which were not verified were not confirmed to be progressing. B. Analysis for root cause was not established immediately after the year 2023 ended.','See correction for dealing with the consequences','2024-07-19','A. 1. Establish alternative schedules for setting CAR verification schedules during the ff: - Internal Audit. - Management Review. - External Audit. 2. Revise Work instruction for CAR verification to reflect current practice: - Requirement to verify CARs within the month instead of the exact day. B.  1. Create a sheet in KPI SCORECARD 2024 MONTHLY REVIEW for recording Annual unmet targets. 2. Scorecards should be completed before every Management Review schedule','2024-07-19','NA-070423-387-IMS','no','2024-07-19','2024-07-18 16:00:00','2024-07-18 16:00:00'),(44,44,'Create a checklist for the releasing of certificates to FAD.','2023-02-24','If we don\'t have a checklist prior to the releasing of certificates to FAD, it may lead to errors such as wrong delivery address and contact number of the participants. If there is no  confirmation of FAD to the participants of there delivery details, there\'s a possibility. No instances of error regarding the details of pax address before sending to FAD (during training, we get the details of pax one by one and explain the reason for the delay or pending of certificates if they will not give their full details then double check before sending to FAD after the training). Non verification of the delivery address the certificates will not be delivered to the client.','Create a checklist prior to the release of certificates to FAD with attached signatories just to make sure that all details are reviewed and complete inorder to avoid error upon delivery','2023-02-24','Indicate/reflect needed fields in conducting a quality checking in the monitoring (delivery details, Reviewed by and Approved by). Assign reviewer and approver.','2023-02-24','no','If the corrective action is not effectively implemented. additional control: conduct orientation of the process  for the new staff','2023-02-24','2023-02-23 16:00:00','2023-02-23 16:00:00'),(45,45,'Enroll Certificate Reference Sheet. Assign staff to update the webinar list info such as the  certificate number- based on Certificate Reference number. Protocol to every assigned staff to complete the details in the webinar list.','2023-02-24','If the webinar list is not updated or incomplete, there\'s a possibility we forgot the certificate number that is assigned in every participant\'s certificate. There\'s a posibility to duplicate the certificate number of every Trainee if the Webinar list is not updated.','Right After the training must update the Certificate number and indicate to webinar list','2023-02-24','Include in the process the completion details for the webinar list . Cascade the revised procedure to the staff. Conduct orientation and review the training process to the staff and inform them of the importance in completing all the details to our webinar list to avoid errors to our certificates. Assign staff to review the webinar list  after training just to make sure that all of the participants\' details had been listed.','2023-02-24','no','no','2023-02-24','2023-02-23 16:00:00','2023-02-23 16:00:00'),(46,46,'Training Supervisor explain to the pax father why his certificate was delayed due to late submission of the requirements prior to printing and then Nagexplain ang Training Supervisor sa tatay ng participants kong bakit hindi naipadala agad yung certificate ng kanyang anak sa kadahilanang late na din eto nagpasa ng mga requirements na ilang ulit ina-announce during training. Nagpacheck din ng participants’ directory ang Supervisor para masiguro na tama ang mailagay sa kanilang mga certificates after ng training. Humingi din ng paumanhin ang Supervisor at magrereprint agad ng panibagong certificate ng kanyang anak at hindi na eto pinabayaran.','2024-08-15','Nagalit yung Tatay ng participant dahil late at mali yung spelling ng name ng kanyang anak sa certificate.','Humingi ng paumanhin ang training supervisor, nagprint ng panibagong certificate at hindi na eto pinabayaran.','2024-08-15','Enforcement of registration per participants before the training and all the details needed for the printing of certificates should be attached to the registration. - Attach a note to the registration form that all the details needed for the printing of certificates are correct otherwise correction of names after printing of the certificates will be charged to the participant. - No more confirmation of the participant’s directory during training, we will rely on the participants registration form.','2024-08-15','no','Checking and inputs of correct name to the certificates should copy on the participants registration forms submitted.','2024-08-15','2024-08-14 16:00:00','2024-08-14 16:00:00'),(47,47,'Pasadahan ang status ng lahat ng mga pending na folders. Unahin ang 2021 na ipaforward sa FAD for billing kahit na wala pang PO / Conforme. Isunod ang 2020 and 2019. Makikipag-coordinate nalang ang FAD sa Sales para sa complete na mga document para sa pagpapareceive ng mga billing at pag-followup ng collection.','2022-08-08','Hindi tumatakbo ang folder, hindi rin mabibill at mababayaran. Nasasayang ang mga nagagastos natin para sa projects na ito.','I-Monitoring ng mahigpit ang closure ng mga projects. I-monitor na walang mapepending na mga folder mula ngayon. (Please see corrective action)','2022-08-08','Ayusin ang monitoring system na madaling madadaanan ng mga SA ang lahat ng kanilang mga pending. Magset ng followup rules at escalation rules para sa mga pending na folders. Starting point ay pagkareceive ng folder mula sa testing. For the first 3 days, daily ang followup ng sales support sa safety associates at dapat rin ifollowup ng mga safety associates ang kailangan na PO/Conforme. Makakatulong dito kung pagkatapos palang ng project makamusta na ng SA ang mga clients para maiproseso na agad ang mga posibleng changes. Kung may mga kailangan na revision (status ay for revision) after 1 week, i-rereport ito sa meeting at i-chcheck ang status kung bakit di parin narerevise ang folder. Regardless kung si SA or si client ang matagal. After 2 weeks, kung wala paring PO/Conforme, gagamit na ng email template ng follow-up at nakalagay dun ang complete details ng project kasama ang proposal, SSR at manghihingi tayo ng acknowledgement of receipt and if pwede na natin ipabill and sa pagpapadala nalang ng billing ay ipapasign na rin ang proposal. Regular emails na mula dito until 1 month. After 1 month, forward na agad ito sa FAD for billing creation and delivery na. Forward ang email thread sa billing & collection staff.','2022-08-08','no','kapag hindi namomonitor ang mga projects hanggang completion, di natin namomonitor kung tama ba ang nagagawa natin, baka may napepending na mga items rin for inspection. Hindi rin makukuha agad ng client ang kanilang certificates na maaaring need na nila for compliance. Close monitoring ng mga projects lalo na ang mga may pending','2022-08-08','2022-08-07 16:00:00','2022-08-07 16:00:00'),(48,48,'Send an email to the client apologizing for the previous bad experience they had with us and guarantee that they won’t experience it again this time around.','2024-02-02','When bad experiences of clients do not reach us and are not addressed, they may become their last impression of us which in turn they may share to others and become a detractor turning away other clients as well.','N/A','2024-02-02','Call the client again in their next renewal schedule (we may need to ask this to the client)  to reintroduce ourselves with the context of the previous bad experience that they won’t experience with us again. If ever Caranzo General Marine & Industrial Services would avail of our services again, prioritize them with our testing department. Emphasize with all SAs that there should be a continuous communication with the clients. This would give us an opportunity to communicate our situation and for them to tell us theirs. If they are in dire need of our services, we could always escalate this to the operations manager. Measure how fast we are able to give inspectors to our clients (w/ respect to their requested schedules). This is to measure how much we are achieving our USP of 48 hours inspection. Make sure that all clients for renewal and churn recoveries are called so that feedbacks like these would be brought to light earlier and allow us to recover our lost clients.','2024-02-02','no','When communication is not complete, we may lose the opportunity to recover clients when we are not able to meet their requirements and expectations. Every SA must be trained on customer experience to make sure they are equipped with the skills to handle client inquiries properly.','2024-02-02','2024-02-01 16:00:00','2024-02-01 16:00:00'),(49,49,'Day 1 concern (jack pallet). The team borrowed a jack pallet from the client to avoid any delays in the inspection activities.  Immediately apologized to the client. Day 2 concern (ladder). The team apologized and explained that our ladder is available. (na binalikan lang ito ng driver sa Batangas Office malapit sa client site dahil hindi kasya sa unang biyahe). Assistant Manager also personally visit the contact person to apologize.','2023-10-05','Customer disappointment since they expect us to bring our own jack pallet and ladder.','Immediately apologized to client and personally visit the contact person.','2023-10-05','For Jack Pallet Concern: - Include in the project implementation plan the double checking of the equipment availability needed on project such as jack pallet, testweights and pallets. Prepare a form/checklist to ensure that all the necessary preparations are considered. - Prepare a clear process on the management of equipment assigned on branches. - Assign person in-charge in the equipment assigned in the Batangas branch. For Ladder Concern: - Reorient ang inspectors kung gaano kahalaaga ang good and constant communication sa contact person including ung mga changes sa plans. (Inform din ang inspectors na if wala ang contact person sa site ay pwede nila itong tawagan at imessage. If hindi ma-contact ay sa ibinigay na mag-aassist ipasuyo na mapadala ang mensahe naten.','2023-10-05','no','This may happen if the jack pallet or other equipment is used in other projects. Include in the project implementation plan the double checking of equipment to be used if available.','2023-10-05','2023-10-04 16:00:00','2023-10-04 16:00:00'),(50,50,'The team attended the Safety Orientation.','2023-09-08','Late start of implementation since orientation is part of the requirement to be able to start the inspection activities.','Adjusted the deployment schedule to ensure that the team can start the implementation the soonest possible.','2023-09-08','Create a standard process for orientation requirements to ensure that all the necessary details are captured and all necessary preparations are conducted. Additional corrective action: install MS Teams to all laptop used for client orientation.','2023-09-08','no','no','2023-09-08','2023-09-07 16:00:00','2023-09-07 16:00:00'),(51,51,'Replaced the duplicate sticker; retain for Phil Nishiyama, replace for Specialized and inform sales and client about the replacement to disregard the initial issued sticker (and QR Code)','2024-02-26','dahil nadoble ang sticker control number na na-release/dikit possible kapag ini-scan ang QR Code iba ang details ng certificate na lumabas may cause confusion sa side ng client at sa possible inspector/auditor.','ininform ang client na papalitan/iisuehan ng bagong sticker ang particular equipment, isinend ang sticker kasabay ng certificate na napalitan na rin ang control number.','2024-02-26','Manpower: Re-orient testing personnel about the proper sorting of sticker based on control number, separating stickers with issues (damaged, error, duplicates). Methods: - Strict Implementation of No Encode, No Deploy on stickers to ensure na walang ma-release na dobleng control number ℅ deployment team. - kapag nakakita/encounter ng sticker na may error lalagyan/susulatan ng label na doble sa likod para maiwasan na maideploy.','2024-02-26','no','no','2024-02-26','2024-02-25 16:00:00','2024-02-25 16:00:00'),(52,52,'Ininform ang client nang needed na compliance para ma-release ang certificate.','2023-12-15','Client Complaint, collect ang details nang concern ng client then nagtanong sa involved na inspectors para ma-cascade sa client ang need na compliance before marelease ang certificate','Verbatim from client: Bakit nauna pa ang soft copy ng na-inspection last Oct. 11 sa na-inspection last Oct. 9? May findings yung gondola kaya pina-hold. Then, sinabi ni SA sa client, paano daw nangyari yun kung sa TSSR walang nakalagay kundi Passed. Tinanong ulit ni SA si technical, ang sabi ng inspector ay verbal lang sinabi sa nag-assist na need ipaayos yung wire rope. As per client, walang sinabi na may ganung findings.','2023-12-15','brainstorm with team and discussion with inspectors on possible situations where certifications may have pending status even after passed at inspection','2023-12-15','no','no','2023-12-15','2023-12-14 16:00:00','2023-12-14 16:00:00'),(53,53,'apologize to client upon arrival on site.','2024-03-08','Customer Complaint, nag advise sa client via text message na possible ma-late ng dating sa site ang team.','N/A','2024-03-08','include in HAIRAC Form for Mobilization/Demobilization of Test Weights; assessment ng area na within operating area ng boom truck and/or any activity na involved ang boom truck.','2024-03-08','VC-050422-135','Dahil hindi pa kasama sa HAIRAC Form ang risk assessment sa area ng operations ng boom truck. Corrective Action: Reminder sa team na involved sa Mobilization/Demobilization ng test weights na need mag conduct ng risk assessment.','2024-03-08','2024-03-07 16:00:00','2024-03-07 16:00:00'),(54,54,'Immediately apologized to the client representative','2024-04-12','Customer complaint','Inspector will inform the client thru text if they will foresee that they will not make it on time to the site location..','2024-04-12','A. I-revise ang format na sinesend sa inspector to include ung time na need sa client at if merong special instructions. B. I-send in advance ang Job Order (soft copy) sa mga inspectors para makita agad ang iinspectionin at if merong special instructions.','2024-04-12','VC-1103-23-161-TES','no','2024-04-12','2024-04-11 16:00:00','2024-04-11 16:00:00'),(55,55,'Scheduled the testing for other equipment (for which the 3 tons weights will be used) inspected other equipment(s) possible on that day','2024-05-31','Client Complaint,','Apologize to client and prioritize their schedule.','2024-05-31','re-cascading/orientation of Test Weight monitoring to personnels which may be involved in deployment incorporate test weight monitoring with deployment sheets frequent review/update of test weight monitoring every project every mobilization of test weights weekly every monday(if no test weight activity) prepare checklist for proper endorsement to deployment in-charge','2024-05-31','no','Add the risk of reschedule and/or extension of project due to weakness on coordination/lack of proper endorsement of tasks. Rating is just low (see risk assement table below)','2024-05-31','2024-05-30 16:00:00','2024-05-30 16:00:00'),(56,56,'1. Sent email to recipients informing the error in the date, particularly double “13” In April. 2. Distribution of remaining calendars was stopped. 3. Manager asked the team to quality-check the other months for errors (none were found). Desk calendars were also checked for any errors (none were found).','2024-03-30','It could potentially harm the image of our brand.','We were able to send out an email blast to the recipients/our clients once we found out the error.','2024-03-30','1. Explore the available options in the canva application. 2. Explore the option of creating the design, then request the outsourced supplier to provide the monthly details. 3. Marketing team should check the accuracy of each day per month (other details of the calendar/collateral should also be considered).  4. Marketing to create a database of the details to be checked on all collaterals.','2024-03-30','NA-112819-143','The potential nonconformity is error in output. It can easily occur thru human error or manual input. Quality checks are done by the team and the suggested corrective actions (refer to corrective action above).','2024-03-30','2024-03-29 16:00:00','2024-03-29 16:00:00');
