INSERT INTO `car_form_processors` VALUES (1,128,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','During the internal audit, it was observed that the auditee did not provide sufficient evidence to support the inclusion of statutory and regulatory requirements for the new service to Isuzu. Specifically, the auditee failed to provide documentation that the new service complies with all applicable laws and regulations. Additionally, the department in charge failed to conduct vendor accreditation for the hired contractor, which means that the contractor\'s qualifications and capabilities have not been verified. This could pose a risk to the company, as the contractor may not be able to provide the required services in a compliant and/or reliable manner.','Brando Estimada/Ralph Oliveros','2023-07-18','Consulting','5th Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-07-17 16:00:00','2024-04-16 16:00:00'),(2,398,'First Issue','Non Audit','Performance Evaluation','Unmet Target for First Pass Yield (Application, Plans) 0% against 40% month of Nov 2023 -- Reviewed Plans & App: Magna Prime','Carolein Licay','2023-12-11','Consulting','1st Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-12-11 16:00:00','2024-01-11 16:00:00'),(3,134,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','The first-pass yield reflected in the KPI scorecard for the month of June is 100%. However, for the project LZN16458, there are comments for revision in the plans which means that the document is not first-pass.','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-04','Consulting','1st Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2024-01-04 16:00:00','2024-04-16 16:00:00'),(4,135,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','The evidence demonstrating the review prior to sending the documents to the client (4th review) is not presented.','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-04','Consulting','1st Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2024-01-04 16:00:00','2024-04-16 16:00:00'),(5,136,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','The form used for the Company Meeting Form as of 21 Sep 2023 is obsolete. It has control number FM No. 06-01-06 but the current enrolled form is FM No. 06-01-20.','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-04','Consulting','2nd Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2024-01-04 16:00:00','2024-04-16 16:00:00'),(6,138,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','There is inaccuracy between the IGR and the reference material (NIST). The IGR recorded the tolerances for Metric Steel Tape under Metric Tape, and vice versa. Also, it was not demonstrated how the department uses these tolerances to determine if the calibrated equipment is still fit for use.','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-04','Consulting','1st Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2024-01-04 16:00:00','2024-08-08 16:00:00'),(7,139,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','There are pieces of equipment that have expired calibration certificates e.g., all metric tape (except CMT-03, CMT-04), metric steel tape (except CMST8-03, CMST8-04), laser distance meter (except CLD150-03, CLD100-04) However, there is no documented evidence that these equipment were pulled-out from the active pool of equipment or segregated.','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-04','Consulting','1st Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2024-01-04 16:00:00','2024-08-08 16:00:00'),(8,140,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','CMST8-06 was calibrated internally last Dec 22, 2022. However, the internal calibration was not conducted in conformance with the WI or reference standard, and thus may not provide accurate measurement evaluation of the relevant equipment.','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-04','Consulting','1st Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2024-01-04 16:00:00','2024-08-08 16:00:00'),(9,351,'FIrst Issue','Non Audit','Performance Evaluation','KPI unmet targets for the month of December 2022 % of Work Plan Completion - Training hrs. per Envi & CCA Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Safety Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Security Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Health & Wellness Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per Communications Subcommittee Member (Competency Building) - Training hrs. per BCP Subcommittee Member (Competency Building)','Brando Estimada','2023-01-18','ESH','5th Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2024-01-17 16:00:00','2023-10-17 16:00:00'),(10,357,'IA-062422-114','Internal Audit','Legal Compliance','Corrective action for the CAR No. IA-062422-114 is not effectively implemented. The process owner has endorsed to its compliance owner the responsibility of updating their own action plans and also distribute listed (google sheets) of established action plans to their respective compliance owners. However, the actions implemented are not effective. There are some actions that are not implemented as scheduled, no remarks for the delay of actions. The update for the document needed as evidence for the compliance is not regularly done','Brando Estimada','2023-01-24','ESH','7th Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-01-30 16:00:00','2024-10-16 16:00:00'),(11,82,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','Presented with an ESH Facility Audit Report (April 2022) and there were some findings that needed actions, However, Person responsible and date of action plan was not identified. Also, some of the action plans in the ESH workplan were not implemented based on the scheduled date (no action taken for the unmet date of implementation if target has been adjusted). ESH BCM No progress on action plans (0% completed) ESH Safety & Security - Security awareness for Security Officer and Subcomm Head not done as scheduled) Risk Management Work Plan','Brando Estimada/Mark Christian Dela Cruz','2022-06-24','ESH','8th Verification',2,2,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2022-06-23 16:00:00','2024-01-18 16:00:00'),(12,120,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','The organization failed to consider potential emergencies that may happen in the client’s site including accidents and incidents, and thus, there is no consider potential emergencies that may happen in established emergency program to address this scenario.','Abigail Gragasin / Nikko Zamora','2023-07-18','ESH','5th Verification',2,3,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-07-17 16:00:00','2024-09-02 16:00:00'),(13,121,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','Also, the ERT manual only contained the process for the monitoring of natural calamities, but not the actual response needed for the emergency such as typhoons or flooding, earthquake, volcanic eruption, etc. Since there is no established response for these natural calamities, there are no planned drills aside from earthquake drill, and there are no identified equipment needed such as for typhoons: emergency lights, alternative food and water supply, etc.','Abigail Gragasin / Nikko Zamora','2023-07-18','ESH','4th Verification',2,3,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-07-17 16:00:00','2024-05-07 16:00:00'),(14,122,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','There is no process to review the status of countermeasures identified in these drills. Also, there is no established process and timeline for the discussion of the results of the actual drill which may cause undue delay for the needed activities or improvements to the EPR.','Abigail Gragasin / Nikko Zamora','2023-07-18','ESH','4th Verification',2,3,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-07-17 16:00:00','2024-09-02 16:00:00'),(15,124,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','The applicability of the organization’s EPR to the contractors was not yet identified and communicated to them.','Abigail Gragasin / Nikko Zamora','2023-07-18','ESH','5th Verification',2,3,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-07-17 16:00:00','2024-09-02 16:00:00'),(16,125,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Process','There are identified equipment and resources needed for EPR but the maintenance of these equipment and resources were not evident','Abigail Gragasin / Nikko Zamora','2023-07-18','ESH','5th Verification',2,3,4,'cmlicay.p360@gmail.com',4,'2023-07-17 16:00:00','2024-09-02 16:00:00'),(17,142,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Emergency Preparedness and Response','The following lapses are found upon auditing the Registry of Hazards and Aspects for ERT: A. There is no documented technical evidence of the basis of changes in the risk rating, especially from moderate to low for the risks identified by the Medical Emergency group. B. The risks from the actual emergency such as earthquake cannot be evaluated appropriately since these were not assessed. C. There is no documented evidence of the conduct of review of the risk registry to establish if there are changes in the risks identified for the Communication and Evacuation group D. There is no conducted review of the registry after the conduct of evacuation drill and the after occurrence of an actual emergency (earthquake)','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-15','ERT','1st Verification',2,2,6,'pgreyes.p360@gmail.com',6,'2024-01-08 16:00:00','2024-09-02 16:00:00'),(18,143,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Emergency Preparedness and Response','Although there is a drill report for the NSED last Nov 9, there is no separate drill report for the medical emergency and communication subgroups that shows the evaluation of each ERT group’s emergency response program. Although \'Use of Fire Extinguisher w/ community\' was conducted, the fire brigade failed to present its drill report. For the Dec 5 Earthquake, the logistics team failed to create a separate report after the emergency.','Abigail Dumayag','2024-01-05','ERT','2nd Verification',2,2,6,'pgreyes.p360@gmail.com',6,'2024-01-08 16:00:00','2024-06-07 16:00:00'),(19,144,'First Issue','Internal Audit','Emergency Preparedness and Response','A. The security team has scheduled drills, but all of them were cancelled. B. No drills are being conducted for the logistics team','Abigail Dumayag','2024-0