sonnel','See verification of corrective action','N/A','For Further Verification','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(7,12,'Segregate uncalibrated tools and label it “Calibration Expired” Per tool, the ones without calibration stickers are deemed not fit for use Schedule External Calibration  Calibrations scheduled in May were done in July as sampled by a certificate below. These were rescheduled since there was a change in the Calibration provider Acculab. We waited for them to renew PAB accreditation. These equipment were stored separately in a box labeled as “Expired Calibration Tools”.','See verification of correction #1','Designate a separate location and storage of pulled-out tools, label all equipment/tools as expired There are Separate Cabinets for Usable tools (Mechanical and Electrical) and tools that are not fit-for-use. Labeling “expired” for each tool not yet done Use Logbook 4 (Logbook for Equipment In and Out & Other Docs) for the Pulled-out tools or equipment. Last pull out for SEM Calaca on May 25, 2024 to be used until October 2024 Attached print-out copy of Calibration Plan to the Mechanical & Electrical Tools Cabinet, for easy distinction between Expired tools and a valid one. Waiting for revision of Calibration plan before attaching to cabinets. Calibration plan to be revised this Aug Cascade this action to all consulting personnel. Discussed during monthly meeting attended by operating personnel','See verification of corrective action','N/A','For Further Verification','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(8,13,'Hold conduct of Internal Calibration Internal Calibration is postponed in 2022 all tools and equipment are calibrated externally since. Rectify tolerance recording The IGR No. 06-01-10 was revised in April. Changes include interchanging contents of metric steel tape to metric tape (See left image for the current version, see right image for the previous version) Remove internally Calibrated Equipment from the official po