INSERT INTO `root_causes` VALUES (1,1,1,'The department was not given enough information on the process of confirming the accreditation and qualification of the subcontractors','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(2,1,2,'The department did not take the initiative to verify to FAD if there is a process to follow before acquiring  subcontractors.','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(3,1,3,'Consulting department and FAD were not aligned in our approach to ensuring compliance and accreditation of sub-contractors, which led to gaps in the process.','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(4,2,1,'Each document is distributed to each member of the team','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(5,2,2,'Staff was new to creating the document.','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(6,2,3,'The staff was not familiar in creating the document','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(7,2,4,'The process was often overlooked. (Ex. Not using the reliable sources such as request for information document, enrolled form, measurement forms)','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(8,2,5,'There is no self checking of the document before proceeding with the review','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(9,3,1,'The data reported for FPY of plans/applications for June is inaccurate','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(10,3,2,'There are errors/discrepancies in the data collection and reporting of the result of the quality check','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(11,3,3,'The criteria for classifying data/inputs as errors or as enhancement opportunities are unclear','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(12,3,4,'Guidelines on quality checking still lack clear expectations for both reviewers and document creators.','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(13,4,1,'Documents that undergo 4 or more rounds of quality checks are not properly documented','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(14,4,2,'The existing internal review form only provides options for up to three rounds of quality checks','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(15,4,3,'Current practice suggests that three internal reviews mark the unofficial limit for document review processes.','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(16,4,4,'Existing review practices are incomplete, lacking specific instructions for documenting the 4th or more reviews of documents','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(17,5,1,'The form (Company Meeting Form) distributed to field personnel is obsolete.','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(18,5,2,'Enrolled and revised forms (that are for enrolment) lack clear labels within the same folder.','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(19,5,3,'Folders are stored on a publicly accessible NAS folder, allowing unauthorized access that leads to misuse of forms','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(20,5,4,'Existing document control within the department isn\'t being strictly followed','method','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(21,6,1,'During the creation of reference (IGR), the tolerances are incorrectly encoded','material','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(22,6,2,'There might be confusion between the tolerance of Metric Steel Tape and Metric Tape','material','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(23,6,3,'The personnel in charge of creating the reference might not be knowledgeable in interpreting NIST standards.','material','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(24,6,1,'Equipment fitness assessments were based solely on calibration certificates','machinery','2024-11-06 16:00:00','2024-11-06 16:00:00'),(25,6,2,'Existing practice for the evaluation of calibrated equipment is inadequate for a holistic assessment of equipment fitness','machin